<HEADLINE>
TRADE FOR CHECO GIVES DODGERS SOME INSURANCE
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BRIAN DOHN  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN DIEGO _ The Los Angeles Dodgers had their eye on
right-handed reliever Robinson Checo before trade talk surfaced
with the Detroit Tigers.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers tried to sign Checo as a free agent during the
offseason, but Checo chose to sign with the Tigers because he liked
his chances to make their club.
</P>
<P>
   With Friday's trade that sent pitchers Dave Mlicki and Mel Rojas
to the Tigers, the Dodgers now have Checo, as well as minor-league
pitchers Apostol Garcia and Richard Roberts.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm not happy for my friends (in Detroit), but I'm happy that
I have a new club and a new chance,'' Checo said before Saturday's
game against San Diego. ``My agent talked with the Dodgers during
(the winter) but it didn't work out.''
</P>
<P>
   Checo, signed originally by the Boston Red Sox after playing in
Japan, will be used in middle relief. The Dodgers like the
27-year-old's ``live arm.'' Checo's fastball has been clocked in
the mid-90s. He also throws a slider, change-up and split-finger
fastball.
</P>
<P>
   General manager Kevin Malone said Checo worked out for the
Dodgers in the Dominican Republic during the offseason.
</P>
<P>
   ``We think he's versatile enough to be an emergency starter or
reliever because he has a powerful arm,'' Malone said. ``(Mlicki)
wasn't going to get the innings.''
</P>
<P>
   Checo is 1-3 with a 5.57 ERA in seven major-league appearances.
</P>
<P>
   Disabled: Kevin Brown has been on the disabled list four times,
but not since May 1996. Darren Dreifort was on the disabled list
twice, but not since June 1997; Carlos Perez's only stint lasted
the 1996 season when he had left shoulder surgery and Ismael Valdes
was on it twice, the most recent being in September.
</P>
<P>
   Chan Ho Park hasn't been on the disabled list.
</P>
<P>
   Balks, walks and chalk: Last Sunday's rainout with Colorado was
rescheduled as part of a day-night doubleheader July 22. A 7:10
p.m. start will be added to the already scheduled 1:10 p.m.
game.... One-time free-swinging right fielder Raul Mondesi drew a
first inning walk, the 10th straight game he's reached base on
balls. It was his 12th walk of the season. He has 12 walks. A year
ago he didn't collect his 11th walk until June 7, the Dodgers' 67th
game.... In the bottom of the first inning LoDuca threw out Quilvio
Veras trying to steal second. It was the first time in 14 attempts
an opponent was thrown out.... The Dodgers' Jacob Brumfield started
in center for Devon White, who was 1 for 19 on the road trip.
</P>
</TEXT>
