<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MAIN _ KUKES, Albania _ Thousands of refugees resumed
their flight from Serbian ethnic cleansing of Kosovo Sunday,
passing the gnarled wreckage of a car that exploded when it hit a
mine in the border no-man's land, killing five members of an
escaping family. Relief agencies reported more refugees arriving
dehydrated and suffering malnutrition, and also bearing bullet
wounds and other injuries. Story will include latest information
from NATO on bombing, ground troops and atrocities. (Kunstel, Cox
News Service) 30.
</P>
<P>
   ALBANIA-SHELLING _ KRUME, Albania _ Accelerated shellings and
explosions the Serbian Yugoslav military are aiming at this craggy
border region are raising fears for the safety of Kosovo refugees,
aid workers and local Albanians. (Kunstel, Cox News Service) 20.
With PHOTOS.
</P>
