   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   FREAKNOT _ Wrapping up what's left of a dead party. Between
noncollege students and cops, there wasn't much left to this year's
Freaknik. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BUSINESS
</P>
<P>
   COMDEX _ CHICAGO _ As two computer pioneers offer rival views
here on Monday, users will be watching to see if in time they adopt
a common strategy. Windows creator Bill Gates and Linux creator
Linus Torvalds will deliver separate keynote speeches at the spring
Comdex/Windows World conference. (Glass, Cox News Service) 25.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   FAIRFAX-BIZ _ AUSTIN _ Jerry Gordon, an economic development
organization president from Fairfax County Virginia, is in town
this week to speak at a conference and possibly drum up business
for his area. His county is economically similar to Austin _
semiconductor companies pump out silicon chips while one large
company (in Gordon's case, America Online) dominates the tech
scene. We look at Austin from a city that reflects many of our
economic qualities. (Gallaga, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   DESIGNER-DEBT _ PALM BEACH, Fla. _ Anna Veksler said her
American dream turned into a nightmare shortly after she entered
into a partnership with Worth Avenue businessman and designer Louis
DiCarlo. The partnership has turned into a raging dispute. Each is
suing the other to dissolve the partnership. (Gelormine, Palm Beach
Post Daily News) MOVED. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
