<P>
   PICASSO-THE-CAR (Paris) _ A new chapter in the saga of Picasso's
heirs is unfolding. Last year Claude Picasso, the artist's
surviving son and the court-appointed administrator of the Picasso
estate, sold the Picasso name and signature to PSA Peugeot-Citroen
for use by the French automaker. But Marina Picasso, the artist's
granddaughter and Claude's niece, has challenged the deal in court.
By Alan Riding.
</P>
