   TV-NEWS-CORRESPONDENTS (Undated) _ The hierarchies and fiefs of
television news are breaking down a bit, driven by the networks'
needs to cut costs and by new management philosophies that see a
need for broadcast news reports to distinguish themselves from the
reporting found on 24-hour cable news networks, radio and the
Internet. As a result, correspondents are contributing reports to
several programs, not just the one to which they are assigned. By
Lawrie Mifflin.
</P>
