   MEDIA-COLUMN (San Francisco) _ The gloom-and-doom predictions
were nothing new to the members of the American Society of
Newspapers Editors, but there was still something arresting about
hearing the chairman of the Intel Corp. saying that the newspaper
business had three years to live. By Felicity Barringer.
