<P>
   &UR; BUNNY &LR;  _ Roughly 74,000 people across the country work in clean
rooms building semiconductors. In the Bay Area, workers don bunny
suits in sophisticated development fabs run by companies such as
Intel, Advanced Micro Devices, National Semiconductor and LSI
Logic. Most local fabs are in Silicon Valley, near their companies'
corporate headquarters. And other fun facts about working in a
clean suit. By Dan Fost
</P>
