<P>
   FBI-JACKSON (WASHINGTON, D.C.) _ The late Sen. Henry Jackson's
ardent support for Israel brought him a string of death threats
laced with vitriolic anti-Semitic rhetoric, according to documents
in the senator's FBI files. The FBI files, obtained by the Seattle
Post-Intelligencer under a Freedom of Information Act request,
reveal for the first time the extent and intensity of threats
against his life.
</P>
<P>
   By Michael Paulson. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
