   (NYT12) NEW YORK -- April 18, 1999 -- HKN-GRETZKY-FATHER, 4-18
-- Wayne Gretzky and his father Walter sharing a moment on the ice
before the Great One's final game of his 21-year pro career at
Madison Square Garden on Sunday. It was a day of mixed emotions for
Walter, 60, who attended the game with his wife, Phyllis, his
daughter-in-law, Janet Jones, and his three grandchildren. ``It
seemed like just yesterday he skated for the first time,'' he said.
``I just can't find the words to say how proud I am of Wayne.''
(Barton Silverman/New York Times Photo)
