   (NYT8) KINNELLON, N.J. -- April 18, 1999 -- ONLINE-VOLUNTEERS,
4-18 -- David Mann, 82, a songwriter and pianist, is a volunteer
for America Online. In exchange for their services, Mann and more
than 10,000 other volunteers get a free account and the designation
``community leader.'' ``I believe that I owe it to the cause of
good music to steer less knowledgeable people in the right
direction,'' says Mann. While Mann considers his role a privilege,
some former volunteers view it as work and have filed complaints
with the Labor Department. (George M. Gutierrez/New York Times
Photo)
