Albanian refugees in Kukes. Since the NATO bombings began more than
three weeks ago, more than 600,000 Albanians have been forced out
of Kosovo, according to the U.N. High Commissioner for Refugees.
Well over half have come to Albania, placing an enormous burden on
aid groups and on Europe's poorest country. (Edward Keating/New
York Times Photo)
